<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><discovery_probe_parameter><active>false</active><name>pfiles-list.sh</name><probe display_value="">e71c56dca9fe156100ae0228d4f4bc97</probe><sys_class_name>discovery_probe_parameter</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>glide.maint</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2007-11-09 19:25:11</sys_created_on><sys_id>25df60300a0a0327004b933f4a54f052</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>pfiles-list.sh</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Core Automation" source="com.snc.core.automation">91d8237704f12210559073c06a02f73b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>discovery_probe_parameter_25df60300a0a0327004b933f4a54f052</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>glide.maint</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2007-11-09 19:25:11</sys_updated_on><value>#!/bin/sh
#
# Determine what processes to get pfile info about...  All if we have no zones
# or only our zone processes if we are zone enabled.
#

IFS="
"
ZONECMD=/usr/bin/zonename

if [ -f $ZONECMD ]; then
        ZONENAME=`$ZONECMD`
        for LINE in `/usr/bin/ps -z $ZONENAME`; do
                PID=`echo $LINE | awk '{print $1}'`
                if [ "$PID" != "PID" -a -f "/proc/$PID/status" ]; then
                        pfiles $PID
                fi
        done
else
        pfiles /proc/*
fi</value><value_script/></discovery_probe_parameter>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><discovery_probe_parameter><active>false</active><name>glsof.sh</name><probe display_value="">578ad1fd0a0a0b200014e0e9a5fe3a3f</probe><sys_class_name>discovery_probe_parameter</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>glide.maint</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2007-08-12 00:49:00</sys_created_on><sys_id>578ae9d70a0a0b2000c62725df94a938</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>glsof.sh</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Core Automation" source="com.snc.core.automation">91d8237704f12210559073c06a02f73b</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>discovery_probe_parameter_578ae9d70a0a0b2000c62725df94a938</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>glide.maint</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2007-08-12 00:49:00</sys_updated_on><value>#!/bin/sh
#
# glsof -- nifty script to get a list of process-to-port information
#
IFS="
"

for i in `netstat -Aanf inet`; do
        SOCKID=`echo $i | awk '{print $1}'`
        LOCAL=`echo $i | awk '{print $5}'`
        REMOTE=`echo $i | awk '{print $6}'`
        STATE=`echo $i | awk '{print $7}'`

        if [[ $LOCAL != "Local" ]]; then
                if [[ $STATE != "" ]]; then
                        echo "$SOCKID:connection:$LOCAL,$REMOTE,$STATE"
                        for x in `echo "sockinfo $SOCKID tcpcb" | kdb | grep pvproc`; do
                                echo "$SOCKID:detail:$x"
                        done
                fi
        fi
done</value><value_script/></discovery_probe_parameter>
